00:21:27,239 --> 00:21:31,551
...but since you can produce
no witnesses of the event--

239
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:36,111
Pardon me. minister.
but as it happens. we can.

240
00:21:39,319 --> 00:21:42,277
Please describe the attack.

241
00:21:44,959 --> 00:21:46,677
What did they look like?

242
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:52,439
Well. one of them was very large
and the other rather skinny.

243
00:21:53,479 --> 00:21:56,198
Not the boys. The Dementors.

244
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:59,875
Oh, right, right. Well, big.

245
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:05,437
Cloaked. Then everything went cold...

246
00:22:06,039 --> 00:22:09,315
...as though all the happiness
had gone from the world.

247
00:22:09,479 --> 00:22:14,348
Now. look here. Dementors don't just
wander into a Muggle suburb...

248
00:22:14,519 --> 00:22:17,989
...and happen across a wizard.
The odds are astronomical.

249
00:22:18,159 --> 00:22:19,831
I don't think anyone would believe...

250
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,912
...the Dementors were there
by coincidence. minister.

251
00:22:25,319 --> 00:22:28,072
I'm sure I must have misunderstood you.
professor.

252
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:33,519
Dementors are. after all. under
the control of the Ministry of Magic.

253
00:22:33,679 --> 00:22:37,718
And it's so silly of me. but it sounded
for a moment as though...

254
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:41,714
...you were suggesting that the Ministry
had ordered the attack on this boy.

255
00:22:41,879 --> 00:22:44,552
That would be disturbing indeed.
Madam Undersecretary...

256
00:22:44,719 --> 00:22:48,712
...which is why I'm sure the Ministry
will be mounting a full-scale inquiry...

257
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:52,111
...into why the two Dementors
were so very far from Azkaban...

258
00:22:52,279 --> 00:22:55,510
...and why they mounted an attack
without authorization.

259
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:58,476
Of course. there is someone...

260
00:22:58,799 --> 00:23:01,313
...who might be behind the attack.

261
00:23:04,199 --> 00:23:08,636
Cornelius. I implore you to see reason.

262
00:23:08,799 --> 00:23:13,156
The evidence that the Dark Lord
has returned is incontrovertible.

263
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:15,993
He is not back.

264
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,756
In the matter of Harry Potter...

265
00:23:24,319 --> 00:23:26,628
...the law clearly states...

266
00:23:26,879 --> 00:23:31,077
...that magic may be used before
Muggles in life-threatening situations.

267
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:34,038
Laws can be changed if necessary.
Dumbledore.

268
00:23:34,199 --> 00:23:37,236
Clearly. Has it become practice
to hold a full criminal trial...

269
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:40,153
...to deal with a simple matter
of underage magic?

270
00:23:48,199 --> 00:23:51,635
Those in favor of conviction?

271
00:24:00,079 --> 00:24:04,834
Those in favor
of clearing the accused of all charges?

272
00:24:18,359 --> 00:24:20,509
Cleared of all charges.

273
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:25,112
Professor.

274
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:40,478
Padfoot. Are you barking mad?

275
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:42,915
You'll blow the entire operation.

276
00:24:50,959 --> 00:24:53,473
Sirius. what are you doing here?
If somebody sees you....

277
00:24:53,639 --> 00:24:56,153
I had to see you off. didn't I?

278
00:24:57,879 --> 00:25:00,268
What's life without a little risk?

279
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:02,710
I don't wanna see you
get chucked back in Azkaban.

280
00:25:02,879 --> 00:25:04,278
Don't worry about me.

281
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:09,470
Anyway. I wanted you to have this.

282
00:25:14,639 --> 00:25:17,551
Original Order of the Phoenix.

283
00:25:18,079 --> 00:25:19,717
Marlene McKinnon.

284
00:25:19,879 --> 00:25:22,347
She was killed
two weeks after this was taken.

285
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:25,757
Voldemort wiped out her entire family.

286
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,878
Frank and Alice Longbottom.

287
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:29,473
Neville's parents.

288
00:25:29,639 --> 00:25:33,154
They suffered a fate worse than death.
you ask me.

289
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:37,395
It's been 14 years.

290
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:42,239
And still a day doesn't go by
I don't miss your dad.

291
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:49,280
Do you really think
there's going to be a war. Sirius?

292
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:54,752
It feels like it did before.

293
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,518
You keep it.

294
00:26:00,999 --> 00:26:05,197
Anyway. I suppose
you're the young ones now.

295
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:09,072
I'll see you at the train.

296
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:11,196
Bye-bye. darling.

297
00:26:12,039 --> 00:26:13,472
I love you.

298
00:26:14,199 --> 00:26:16,110
Hold my hand. Iovey.

299
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:18,555
There they are.
They're in the far carriage.

300
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:19,948
Bye.

301
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:03,238
I'm surprised the Ministry's
still letting you walk around free.

302
00:27:03,399 --> 00:27:04,832
Better enjoy it while you can.

303
00:27:04,999 --> 00:27:08,150
I expect there's a cell in Azkaban
with your name on it.

304
00:27:10,639 --> 00:27:14,427
-What'd I tell you? Complete nutter.
-Just stay away from me!

305
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,352
It's only Malfoy.

306
00:27:18,159 --> 00:27:19,911
What'd you expect?

307
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:40,195
Hi. guys.

308
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:41,952
-Hey. Neville.
-Hey there. Neville.

309
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,959
What is it?

310
00:27:58,040 --> 00:28:01,157
-What's what?
-That. Pulling the carriage.

311
00:28:01,959 --> 00:28:04,189
Nothing's pulling the carriage. Harry.

312
00:28:04,799 --> 00:28:06,915
It's pulling itself. like always.

313
00:28:19,999 --> 00:28:22,115
You're not going mad.

314
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,750
I can see them too.

315
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:30,428
You're just as sane as I am.

316
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:37,036
Everyone. this is Loony Love--

317
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:41,551
Luna Lovegood.

318
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:47,550
What an interesting necklace.

319
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:50,150
It's a charm. actually.

320
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:52,993
Keeps away the Nargles.

321
00:28:56,639 --> 00:28:58,072
Hungry.

322
00:28:58,719 --> 00:29:00,596
I hope there's pudding.

323
00:29:01,559 --> 00:29:04,995
-What's a Nargle?
-No idea.

324
00:29:17,199 --> 00:29:18,757
Good evening. children.

325
00:29:19,999 --> 00:29:22,593
Now. we have two changes
in staffing this year.

326
00:29:22,759 --> 00:29:25,671
We're pleased to welcome back
Professor Grubbly-Plank...

327
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:28,308
...who'll be taking
Care of Magical Creatures...

328
00:29:28,479 --> 00:29:31,789
...while Professor Hagrid
is on temporary leave.

329
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:36,434
We also wish to welcome our new
Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher...

330
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:39,637
...Professor Dolores Umbridge.

331
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:43,515
And I'm sure you'll all join me
in wishing the professor good luck.

332
00:29:44,279 --> 00:29:49,069
Now. as usual. our caretaker. Mr. Filch.
has asked me to remind you--

333
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:02,314
She was at my hearing.
She works for Fudge.

334
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:07,952
Thank you. headmaster.
for those kind words of welcome.

335
00:30:09,279 --> 00:30:12,794
And how lovely to see all your bright...

336
00:30:12,960 --> 00:30:15,679
...happy faces smiling up at me.

337
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:20,989
I'm sure we're all going
to be very good friends.

338
00:30:21,159 --> 00:30:23,309
-That's likely.
-That's likely.

339
00:30:26,039 --> 00:30:28,872
The Ministry of Magic
has always considered...

340
00:30:29,039 --> 00:30:34,432
...the education of young witches
and wizards to be of vital importance.

341
00:30:34,759 --> 00:30:36,954
Although each headmaster...

342
00:30:37,119 --> 00:30:41,749
...has brought something new
to this historic school...

343
00:30:43,239 --> 00:30:49,155
...progress for the sake of progress
must be discouraged.

344
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:53,515
Let us preserve
what must be preserved...

345
00:30:53,679 --> 00:30:57,035
...perfect what can be perfected...

346
00:30:57,200 --> 00:31:03,548
...and prune practices
that ought to be prohibited.

347
00:31:10,319 --> 00:31:14,278
Thank you. Professor Umbridge.
That really was most illuminating.

348
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:18,592
-|||uminating? What a load of waffle.
-What's it mean?

349
00:31:19,319 --> 00:31:21,389
Magic is forbidden in the corridors....

350
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:24,996
It means the Ministry's
interfering at Hogwarts.

351
00:31:43,959 --> 00:31:45,631
Dean. Seamus.

352
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:47,956
-Good holiday?
-All right.

353
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:50,436
Better than Seamus'. anyway.

354
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:53,950
Me mum didn't want me
to come back this year.

355
00:31:54,119 --> 00:31:57,270
-Why not?
-Let me see. Because of you.

356
00:31:57,680 --> 00:32:00,911
The Daily Prophet's been saying a lot
of things about you and Dumbledore.

357
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:02,354
What. your mum believes them?

358
00:32:02,519 --> 00:32:04,350
Nobody was there
the night Cedric died.

359
00:32:04,519 --> 00:32:07,477
I guess you should read the Prophet,
then. like your stupid mother.

360
00:32:07,639 --> 00:32:10,995
-Don't talk about my mother.
-|'|| have a go at anyone calling me a liar.

361
00:32:11,159 --> 00:32:13,548
-What's going on?
-He's mad. is what's going on.

362
00:32:13,719 --> 00:32:16,677
Do you believe the rubbish he's
come out with about You-Know-Who?

363
00:32:16,840 --> 00:32:18,432
Yeah. I do.

364
00:32:19,399 --> 00:32:21,276
Has anyone else
got a problem with Harry?

365
00:32:30,320 --> 00:32:32,629
-You all right?
-Fine.

366
00:32:32,799 --> 00:32:35,472
Seamus was bang out of order. mate.

367
00:32:36,039 --> 00:32:39,634
-But he'll come through. you'll see.
-I said. I'm fine. Ron.

368
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:47,392
Right. I'll just leave you
to your thoughts. then.

369
00:33:14,639 --> 00:33:15,628
Harry.

370
00:33:30,439 --> 00:33:32,509
Bring it over here. Over here.

371
00:33:33,399 --> 00:33:36,152
Oh. go on. Seamus. Go on. get it.

372
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:52,513
Good morning. children.

373
00:33:54,439 --> 00:33:59,388
Ordinary Wizarding Level examinations.

374
00:33:59,560 --> 00:34:02,028
O-W-Ls.

375
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:06,591
More commonly known as OWLs.

376
00:34:06,759 --> 00:34:09,751
Study hard and you will be rewarded.

377
00:34:10,079 --> 00:34:15,107
Fail to do so.
and the consequences may be severe.

378
00:34:20,479 --> 00:34:25,314
Your previous instruction in this subject
has been disturbingly uneven.

379
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:27,550
But you'll be pleased to know.
from now on...

380
00:34:27,719 --> 00:34:31,075
...you will be following a carefully
structured. Ministry-approved...

381
00:34:31,239 --> 00:34:33,799
...course of defensive magic. Yes?

382
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:37,594
There's nothing in here
about using defensive spells?

383
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:39,239
Using spells?

384
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:42,710
Well. I can't imagine why you would
need to use spells in my classroom.

385
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:45,873
We're not gonna use magic?

386
00:34:46,039 --> 00:34:50,829
You'll be learning about defensive spells
in a secure. risk-free way.

387
00:34:50,999 --> 00:34:53,638
What use is that?
If we're attacked. it won't be risk-free.

388
00:34:53,799 --> 00:34:56,632
Students will raise their hands
when they speak in my class.

389
00:35:00,119 --> 00:35:02,428
It is the view of the Ministry...

390
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:05,239
...that a theoretical knowledge
will be sufficient...

391
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:07,277
...to get you through
your examinations...

392
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:09,795
...which. after all.
is what school is all about.

393
00:35:09,959 --> 00:35:12,632
And how's theory supposed
to prepare us for what's out there?

394
00:35:12,799 --> 00:35:14,755
There is nothing out there. dear.

395
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:17,798
Who do you imagine
wants to attack children like yourself?

396
00:35:17,959 --> 00:35:21,110
Oh. I don't know.
Maybe Lord Voldemort.

397
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:35,672
Now. let me make this quite plain.

398
00:35:36,199 --> 00:35:37,598
You have been told...

399
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:42,914
...that a certain dark wizard
is at large once again.

400
00:35:43,079 --> 00:35:47,994
-This is a lie.
-|t's not a lie. I saw him. I fought him.

401
00:35:48,160 --> 00:35:49,718
Detention. Mr. Potter.

402
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,950
Cedric Diggory dropped dead
of his own accord?

403
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:54,429
Cedric Diggory's death
was a tragic accident.

404
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:56,670
It was murder. Voldemort killed him.

405
00:35:56,839 --> 00:35:58,272
Enough!

406
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:00,512
Enough.

407
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:04,832
See me later. Mr. Potter. My office.

408
00:36:28,560 --> 00:36:29,709
Come in.

409
00:36:34,759 --> 00:36:36,590
Good evening. Mr. Potter.

410
00:36:37,199 --> 00:36:38,427
Sit.

411
00:36:45,799 --> 00:36:49,553
You're going to be doing some lines
for me today. Mr. Potter.

412
00:36:49,719 --> 00:36:51,516
No. not with your quill.

413
00:36:51,719 --> 00:36:54,791
Going to be using
a rather special one of mine.

414
00:36:59,719 --> 00:37:01,072
Now...

415
00:37:01,999 --> 00:37:07,631
...I want you to write.
“I must not tell lies.“

416
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:11,437
How many times?

417
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:16,351
Well. let's say for as long as it takes
for the message to sink in.

418
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:19,872
You haven't given me any ink.

419
00:37:20,039 --> 00:37:21,472
Oh. you won't need any ink.

420
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:12,033
Yes?

421
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:22,311
-Nothing.
-That's right.

422
00:38:23,199 --> 00:38:26,987
Because you know. deep down...

423
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:29,151
...you deserve to be punished.

424
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:32,350
Don't you. Mr. Potter?

425
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:37,958
Go on.

426
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:48,795
-Skiving Snackboxes.
-Sweets that make you ill.

427
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,518
Get out of class whenever you like.

428
00:38:50,680 --> 00:38:54,275
Obtain hours of pleasure
from unprofitable boredom.

429
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:56,514
Care for another?

430
00:38:56,680 --> 00:38:59,114
-|'m not asking you to write all of it.
-P|ease.

431
00:38:59,279 --> 00:39:02,112
I've been busy studying
for these stupid OWL exams.

432
00:39:02,599 --> 00:39:04,317
I'll do the introduction. That's all.

433
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:08,075
Hermione. you're honestly the most
wonderful person I've ever met.

434
00:39:08,239 --> 00:39:12,312
-And if I'm ever rude to you again....
-|'|| know you've gone back to normal.

435
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:19,151
What's wrong with your hand?

436
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:21,079
Nothing.

437
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:24,111
The other hand.

438
00:39:26,519 --> 00:39:28,271
-You've got to tell Dumbledore.
-No.

439
00:39:28,439 --> 00:39:30,555
Dumbledore's got enough
on his mind right now.

440
00:39:30,719 --> 00:39:32,755
I don't want to give
Umbridge the satisfaction.

441
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:35,229
Bloody hell. Harry.
The woman's torturing you.

442
00:39:35,399 --> 00:39:39,187
-If the parents knew about this....
-I haven't got any of those. have I. Ron?

443
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:44,235
Harry. you've got to report this.

444
00:39:44,399 --> 00:39:47,789
-|t's perfectly simple. You're being--
-No. it's not.

445
00:39:47,959 --> 00:39:50,678
Hermione. whatever this is.
it's not simple.

446
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:53,636
You don't understand.

447
00:39:56,119 --> 00:39:57,950
Then help us to.

448
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:13,877
Dear Padloot...

449
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:16,038
...I hope you're all right.

450
00:40:16,199 --> 00:40:20,636
It's starting to get colder here.
Winter is definitely on the way.

451
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:27,711
In spite of being back at Hogwarts,
I feel more alone than ever.

452
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:31,717
I know you, of all people,
will understand.

453
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:06,516
Hello. Harry Potter.

454
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:13,477
-Your feet. Aren't they cold?
-Bit.

455
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:18,239
Unfortunately. all my shoes
have mysteriously disappeared.

456
00:41:18,759 --> 00:41:21,717
I suspect Nargles are behind it.

457
00:41:27,799 --> 00:41:31,269
-What are they?
-They're called Thestrals.

458
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:36,789
They're quite gentle. really. but people
avoid them because they're a bit....

459
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:41,158
Different.

460
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:46,435
But why can't the others see them?

461
00:41:46,600 --> 00:41:49,956
They can only be seen
by people who've seen death.

462
00:41:51,999 --> 00:41:54,513
So you've known someone
who's died. then?

463
00:41:54,680 --> 00:41:56,238
My mum.

464
00:41:56,759 --> 00:42:01,469
She was quite an extraordinary witch.
but she did like to experiment...

465
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:04,791
...and one day.
one of her spells went badly wrong.

466
00:42:04,959 --> 00:42:07,234
-I was 9.
-|'m sorry.

467
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:09,916
Yes. it was rather horrible.

468
00:42:10,079 --> 00:42:15,199
I do feel very sad about it sometimes.
but I've got Dad.

469
00:42:17,320 --> 00:42:19,880
We both believe you. by the way.

470
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:25,678
That He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named
is back. and you fought him...

471
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:28,832
...and the Ministry and the Prophet
are conspiring against you.

472
00:42:28,999 --> 00:42:33,151
Thanks. It seems you're about
the only ones that do.

473
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,594
I don't think that's true.

474
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:39,872
But I suppose
that's how he wants you to feel.

475
00:42:40,039 --> 00:42:41,757
What do you mean?

476
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:44,157
Well. if I were You-Know-Who...

477
00:42:44,599 --> 00:42:48,035
...I'd want you to feel cut off
from everyone else...

478
00:42:48,199 --> 00:42:50,793
...because if it's just you alone...

479
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:53,830
...you're not as much of a threat.

480
00:43:10,759 --> 00:43:15,310
-Do you ever stop eating?
-What? I'm hungry.

481
00:43:18,559 --> 00:43:19,548
Harry.

482
00:43:21,319 --> 00:43:22,513
Can I join you?

