I'll make this simple for you. Potter.

1227
01:49:50,920 --> 01:49:54,117
Give me the prophecy now...

1228
01:49:54,280 --> 01:49:58,114
...or watch your friends die.

1229
01:50:10,519 --> 01:50:11,872
Don't give it to him. Harry.

1230
01:50:37,080 --> 01:50:39,719
Get away from my godson.

1231
01:51:08,599 --> 01:51:11,067
Now. listen to me.
Take the others and get out of here.

1232
01:51:11,400 --> 01:51:13,152
What? No. I'm staying with you.

1233
01:51:13,319 --> 01:51:16,038
You've done beautifully.

1234
01:51:16,679 --> 01:51:18,237
Now. let me take it from here.

1235
01:51:18,400 --> 01:51:19,389
Black.

1236
01:51:45,439 --> 01:51:46,713
Exp elliarm us!

1237
01:51:46,880 --> 01:51:48,154
Nice one. James.

1238
01:51:55,080 --> 01:51:56,513
Avada Kedavra.

1239
01:52:15,880 --> 01:52:18,110
No. No.

1240
01:52:41,160 --> 01:52:43,628
I killed Sirius Black.

1241
01:52:44,560 --> 01:52:46,437
-You coming to get me?
-Crucio.

1242
01:52:58,280 --> 01:53:01,317
You've got to mean it, Harry.

1243
01:53:01,479 --> 01:53:05,074
She killed him. She deserves it.

1244
01:53:08,760 --> 01:53:11,832
You know the spell, Harry.

1245
01:53:22,919 --> 01:53:24,477
Do it.

1246
01:53:31,840 --> 01:53:34,673
So weak.

1247
01:53:41,160 --> 01:53:44,232
It was foolish of you
to come here tonight. Tom.

1248
01:53:44,400 --> 01:53:46,072
The Aurors are on their way.

1249
01:53:46,240 --> 01:53:50,279
By which time I shall be gone.
and you...

1250
01:53:51,720 --> 01:53:53,756
...shall be dead.

1251
01:56:02,560 --> 01:56:04,357
You've lost. old man.

1252
01:56:23,680 --> 01:56:24,669
Harry.

1253
01:56:28,639 --> 01:56:30,072
So weak.

1254
01:56:30,559 --> 01:56:32,675
So vulnerable.

1255
01:56:36,800 --> 01:56:37,789
Look at me.

1256
01:56:40,200 --> 01:56:44,273
Harry. it isn't how you are alike.

1257
01:56:44,440 --> 01:56:46,829
It's how you are not.

1258
01:56:51,559 --> 01:56:52,992
Harry?

1259
01:57:24,079 --> 01:57:25,478
You're the weak one...

1260
01:57:26,079 --> 01:57:30,038
...and you'll never know
love or friendship.

1261
01:57:33,319 --> 01:57:36,072
And I feel sorry for you.

1262
01:57:58,199 --> 01:58:01,509
You're a fool. Harry Potter.

1263
01:58:02,440 --> 01:58:07,355
And you will lose everything.

1264
01:58:21,680 --> 01:58:23,272
He's back.

1265
01:59:28,239 --> 01:59:29,831
I know how you feel. Harry.

1266
01:59:29,999 --> 01:59:31,557
No. you don't.

1267
01:59:36,959 --> 01:59:38,278
It's my fault.

1268
01:59:38,440 --> 01:59:41,591
No. the fault is mine.

1269
01:59:42,560 --> 01:59:44,232
I knew it was only a matter of time...

1270
01:59:44,400 --> 01:59:47,358
...before Voldemort made the connection
between you.

1271
01:59:48,119 --> 01:59:52,192
I thought by distancing myself from you.
as I have done all year...

1272
01:59:52,359 --> 01:59:57,387
...he'd be less tempted. and therefore
you might be more protected.

1273
02:00:00,079 --> 02:00:03,276
The prophecy said:

1274
02:00:03,879 --> 02:00:07,667
“Neither one can live
while the other one survives.“

1275
02:00:08,959 --> 02:00:14,750
It means one of us is gonna
have to kill the other. in the end.

1276
02:00:16,680 --> 02:00:18,193
Yes.

1277
02:00:18,639 --> 02:00:20,152
Why didn't you tell me?

1278
02:00:20,319 --> 02:00:23,755
For the same reason
you tried to save Sirius.

1279
02:00:23,919 --> 02:00:26,274
The same reason your friends saved you.

1280
02:00:27,079 --> 02:00:30,435
After all these years.
after all you've suffered...

1281
02:00:30,599 --> 02:00:33,397
...I didn't want to cause you
any more pain.

1282
02:00:34,800 --> 02:00:36,836
I cared too much about you.

1283
02:01:00,680 --> 02:01:02,910
How come you're not at the feast?

1284
02:01:03,079 --> 02:01:07,436
Lost all my possessions. Apparently
people have been hiding them.

1285
02:01:07,599 --> 02:01:08,588
That's awful.

1286
02:01:08,759 --> 02:01:10,556
Oh. it's all good fun.

1287
02:01:10,719 --> 02:01:14,029
But as it's the last night.
I really do need them back.

1288
02:01:14,199 --> 02:01:16,474
Do you want any help finding them?

1289
02:01:19,240 --> 02:01:22,312
I'm sorry about your godfather. Harry.

1290
02:01:29,079 --> 02:01:31,070
Are you sure you don't want
any help looking?

1291
02:01:31,240 --> 02:01:32,832
That's all right.

1292
02:01:32,999 --> 02:01:35,069
Anyway. my mum always said...

1293
02:01:35,239 --> 02:01:38,914
...the things we lose have a way
of coming back to us in the end.

1294
02:01:42,040 --> 02:01:45,157
If not always in the way we expect.

1295
02:01:46,599 --> 02:01:49,193
Think I'll just go have some pudding.

1296
02:02:23,399 --> 02:02:26,197
I've been thinking about something
Dumbledore said to me.

1297
02:02:26,359 --> 02:02:27,997
What's that?

1298
02:02:28,559 --> 02:02:31,232
That even though
we've got a fight ahead of us...

1299
02:02:31,400 --> 02:02:34,358
...we've got one thing
that Voldemort doesn't have.

1300
02:02:34,519 --> 02:02:35,952
Yeah?

1301
02:02:37,799 --> 02:02:40,029
Something worth fighting for.

1302
02:12:27,680 --> 02:12:29,671
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group

1303
02:12:29,839 --> 02:12:31,830
[ENGLISH]

